
[1]dome

   DOME, n. [Gr., a house, a plain roof. L.]

   1. A building; a house; a fabric; used in poetry.

   2. A cathedral.

   3. In architecture, a spherical roof, raised over the middle of a
   building; a cupola.

   4. In chemistry, the upper part of a furnace, resembling a hollow
   hemisphere or small dome. This form serves to reflect or reverberate a
   part of the flame; hence these furnaces are called reverberating
   furnaces.
